@PrivacyAnalytics.Api_HostAddress = http://localhost:5115

### Track endpoint — Tier 1 (anonymous): no X-User-Id → SHA-256(IP + UA + DailySalt) is
### computed and DurableHash is null. AnonymousDailyHash is forced null whenever IsAuthenticated
### is true, so this branch is the only one that populates it.
POST {{PrivacyAnalytics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/track
X-Tenant-Origin: acme.example.com
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://shop.example.com/products/widget?email=user@example.com&ref=affiliate123",
  "referralSource": "https://google.com/search?q=widgets",
  "eventType": "pageview"
}

### Track endpoint — Tier 2 (authenticated, opted in): X-User-Id present + X-User-Opted-In: true
### → tenant-scoped DurableHash is computed. Note AnonymousDailyHash is logged <null> even though
### the IP/UA are available: this is the FR-2.1 forced-null rule preventing double-counting between
### tiers. X-Tenant-Id scopes the HMAC so the same user in two tenants hashes differently.
POST {{PrivacyAnalytics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/track
X-Tenant-Origin: acme.example.com
X-Tenant-Id: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
X-User-Id: auth0|user-42
X-User-Opted-In: true
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://shop.example.com/products/widget",
  "eventType": "pageview"
}

### Track endpoint — authenticated but NOT opted in: no identifier is stored at all
### (AnonymousDailyHash = null AND DurableHash = null). Correct privacy posture.
POST {{PrivacyAnalytics.Api_HostAddress}}/api/v1/track
X-Tenant-Origin: acme.example.com
X-Tenant-Id: 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
X-User-Id: auth0|user-42
X-User-Opted-In: false
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://shop.example.com/products/widget",
  "eventType": "pageview"
}

### Track endpoint — same tenant, expected to 429 once >100 req/sec arrive.
### Send 105 rapid requests; the last ~5 should return 429 Too Many Requests.
###
